      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAJOR REASON (8) won the last time he raced here three back and has finished within 4m of the winner in his two Menangle outings since. Draws wide but owns a good record at this distance so is well placed. SUNSET STRIDE (2) started favourite here last week but was held up and finished third, beaten 4 metres. Should enjoy a nice run from a favourable starting position so could atone. MR TEDDY NZ (9) looks close to a win after finishing runner-up in three of his last four outings. Draws for a trail and is a player if he gets the gaps. PETES CRUNCH TIME (7) hasn't been too far away in the city of late and is suited returning to a venue where he has recorded four wins and two placings from nine attempts.",
